<nowiki>{{Weekday before date|Y|M|D|W}}</nowiki> returns the date of the first W (=Sunday, Monday, ..., Saturday) before the specified date with year Y, month M, and day of month D.

The first Sunday before {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTDAY}}, {{CURRENTYEAR}} is given by "<nowiki>{{Weekday before date|</nowiki>{{CURRENTYEAR}}|{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}}|{{CURRENTDAY}}<nowiki>|Sunday}}</nowiki>" as "{{Weekday before date|{{CURRENTYEAR}}|{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}}|{{CURRENTDAY}}|Sunday}}".

Optionally you can format the output using the fifth parameter. For example the first Sunday before {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTDAY}}, {{CURRENTYEAR}} is given by "<nowiki>{{Weekday before date|</nowiki>{{CURRENTYEAR}}|{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}}|{{CURRENTDAY}}<nowiki>|Sunday|d M y}}</nowiki>" as "{{Weekday before date|{{CURRENTYEAR}}|{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}}|{{CURRENTDAY}}|Sunday|d M y}}".
 
See also [[Template:Weekday after Julianday]] and [[Template:Weekday after date]].
